description: CGTN  added  4 new photos . ‘Oldest girl in Asia’ dies at 19 with body age of 150  A teenager dubbed the “oldest girl in Asia” died last week aged 19 from a rare condition that rapidly aged her body – she passed away with a body age of 150 years.  Filipino teenager Ana Rocelle suffered from Hutchinson-Gilford progeria syndrome, which causes the body to age eight times faster than normal. The typical cause of death is either heart attack or stroke.   Though Ana did not enjoy a long life, she lived her time to the full. On her 18th birthday she had a princess-themed party with a throne and multiple costume changes. She also snapped selfies with her idol, Filipino singer Sarah Geronimo.   Ana’s death was reported by US-based charity Progeria Research Foundation, which campaigns for sufferers of the genetic condition.

The painting dates from around 1500 and is one of the last remaining da Vinci paintings in private hands. It is expected to sell for 100 million US dollars.  Unaware of its true history, the painting was bought in America, at a small auction house for less than ten thousand US dollars.
